==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek adjective [[ἡμιόλιος]] (''hemiolios''), meaning "containing one and a half," "half as much again," "in the ratio of one and a half to one (3:2), as in musical sounds"

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|music}} The [[articulation]] of two [[bar]]s in [[triple]] time as if they were three bars in [[duple]] time.

